## Docs Ingestion

Mini support-bot pipeline for scraping support articles, converting them to Markdown, loading them into Gemini File Search, and running an OptiBot-style assistant with citations.

### Results

- Scraped 30 support articles from `support.optisigns.com`.
- Converted articles into slug-based Markdown files in `data/markdown/`.
- Uploaded Markdown files to Gemini File Search by API, not manual UI upload.
- Chunking uses whitespace chunks: 300 tokens per chunk, 50 token overlap.
- Daily ingestion runs through `src/main.py`: re-scrape, convert, detect hash changes, upload only changed files, and log added/updated/skipped counts.
- Latest local run: `scraped_articles=30`, `changed_or_new_files=0`, `skipped_unchanged_files=30`, `upload_success=0`.
- Live app: https://docs-ingestion.onrender.com/
- Render cron schedule: `45 5 * * *`, which runs daily at 05:45 UTC / 12:45 Vietnam time.

### Setup

Copy env sample: `cp .env.sample .env`

Fill required values in `.env`: `GEMINI_API_KEY` and `FILE_SEARCH_STORE_NAME`.

Install: `pip install -r requirements.txt`

### How To Run Locally

Run ingestion once: `python src/main.py`

Ask any question from terminal: `python src/ask_bot.py "How do I add a YouTube video?"`

Example with another question: `python src/ask_bot.py "How do I pre-configure Wi-Fi?"`

Run Streamlit UI: `streamlit run src/app.py`

Run Docker job once with `.env`: `docker build -t docs-ingestion .` then `docker run --rm --env-file .env docs-ingestion`

Run Docker job once with explicit env vars: `docker run --rm -e GEMINI_API_KEY=your_key -e FILE_SEARCH_STORE_NAME=your_store_name -e BASE_URL=https://support.optisigns.com -e LOCALE=en-us -e MAX_ARTICLES=30 docs-ingestion`

Run Docker UI: `docker compose up --build`, then open `http://localhost:8501`.

`Dockerfile` is intentionally the one-shot ingestion job required by the test. `Dockerfile.web` is only for the long-running Streamlit demo service.

### Deploy

Render uses `render.yaml`:

- `docs-assistant-ui`: Streamlit web UI, built from `Dockerfile.web`.
- `docs-ingestion-daily`: daily cron job, built from `Dockerfile`, running `python src/main.py`.
- Cron time: every day at 05:45 UTC / 12:45 Vietnam time.

Required Render env vars: `GEMINI_API_KEY`, `FILE_SEARCH_STORE_NAME`, `BASE_URL`, `LOCALE`, `MAX_ARTICLES`.

Daily job logs are available in the Render dashboard under `docs-ingestion-daily` logs/events. Local run artifacts are JSON files in `logs/`.

